text.section:
The provisions of subsection A shall apply to felony convictions for:

Carnal knowledge of a child between 13 and 15 years of age in violation of § 18.2-63 when the offense is committed by a person over the age of 18;


Carnal knowledge of certain minors in violation of § 18.2-64.1;


Aggravated sexual battery in violation of § 18.2-67.3;


Crimes against nature in violation of subsection B of § 18.2-361;


Sexual intercourse with one's own child or grandchild in violation of § 18.2-366;


Taking indecent liberties with a child in violation of § 18.2-370 or 18.2-370.1; or


Conspiracy to commit any offense listed in subdivisions 1 through 6 pursuant to § 18.2-22.
